As of the census<ref name="census2">{{cite web |title=U.S. Census website |url=https://www.census.gov |accessdate=May 23, 2011 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref> of 2010, there were 400 people living in the CDP. There were 164 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|racial makeup]] of the town was 91.5% White, 0.3% American Indian and Alaska Native, 6.0% from some other race, and 2.3% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 8.8% of the population.

